Statement) Which CSS transform property is used to rotate an element clockwise or counterclockwise?
rotate
spin
flip
turn

-----------------------------------
SOLUTION = 
The correct answer is: rotate

----------------------
Code Usage:- .rotated-element {
  transform: rotate(45deg); /* Rotate 45 degrees clockwise */
}

--------------------
Explanation:

rotate property: The rotate() function within the transform property is used to rotate an element around its center point. It accepts a single value, which specifies the angle of rotation in degrees.

Positive values rotate clockwise.
Negative values rotate counterclockwise.
Other transformation properties:

translate(): Moves an element along the X and/or Y axis.
scale(): Scales an element in size.
skew(): Skews an element along one or both axes.
matrix(): Applies a 2D transformation matrix for more complex transformations.
Example:

The provided code will rotate any element with the class rotated-element 45 degrees clockwise.

